  <title>Virtual CDROM</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>ATAPI</keyword>
    <keyword>dqa0</keyword>
    <keyword>ISO</keyword>
    <keyword>media</keyword>
    <keyword>option firmware</keyword>
    <keyword>RUN/STOP</keyword>
    <keyword>virtual CDROM</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header><para styleclass="Heading1">Virtual CDROM</para></header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Code Example">dqa0</text> (&quot;EMULATR VIRTUAL CDROM&quot;) is the virtual optical device the firmware probes for option firmware during power-up. When no media is present it reports &quot;no media present or is disabled via the RUN/STOP switch&quot;.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">An ISO image is supplied (not created) through a manifest storage entry: an ATAPI / CD-ROM <text styleclass="Code Example">type</text> with the <text styleclass="Code Example">media</text> set to the ISO file. The optical device is read-only, so <text styleclass="Code Example">create_if_missing</text> never applies to it. ISO contents are read through the ISO-9660 path (see ISO-9660 PFD).</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-style:italic;">[TODO: confirm the exact manifest type/key for attaching an ISO to dqa0 against the current build.]</text></para>
